author: Daniel Kilkelly
title: UK TV ratings: Coronation Street ahead on Friday despite timeslot change - Coronation Street Soaps -
text: Coronation Street topped the ratings on Friday (October 9) despite being moved out of its regular timeslot, overnight figures show.The Weatherfield soap managed 5.3m (29.3%) at the earlier time of 6.45pm on ITV as Kylie was forced to share the secret of Callum's final resting place with Sarah, adding 343k (1.7%) on +1. © ITVSarah and Kylie in Friday's Coronation Street Airing against the England vs. Estonia game, EastEnders managed 5.14m (24.6%) at 8pm on BBC One as Ian demanded answers from Kathy and Ben discovered that his mum is still alive. BBC Three's repeat screening secured 367k (2.2%) at 10pm.Neighbours appealed to 696k (11.9%) at 1.45pm and 629k (4.7%) at 5.30pm on Channel 5 as Naomi discovered Paul's latest scheme.Doctors continued with 1.25m (21.5%) at 1.45pm on BBC One as Daniel offered some harsh advice to Howard. © BBCDaniel in Doctors Hollyoaks mustered 655k (3.8%) at 6.30pm on Channel 4 as Ben rushed to rescue Sienna from the fire (+1: 92k / 0.5%), while E4's first look had 444k (2.6%) at 7pm (+1: 44k / 0.2%).Home and Away grabbed 181k (3.0%) at 1.15pm and 455k (2.9%) at 6pm on Channel 5, while 5*'s first look had 306k (1.8%) at 6.30pm.
